    "body": "For reference, newline stripping becomes as straightforward as:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nfn main() {\r\n    println!(\"{:?}\", \"mysupersecurepassword\\r\\n\".trim_end_matches(|c| c == '\\r' || c == '\\n'));\r\n    println!(\"{:?}\", \"mysupersecurepassword\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\r\".trim_end_matches(|c| c == '\\r' || c == '\\n'));\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n[Playground Link](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=afa6fa034aeae3b0551d472682637904)\r\n\r\nWhich is simpler than working with bytes as in #1199",
